Miscellaneous Highlights: India's tour to Ireland has managed to fill the stands over the years, making it a fruitful opportunity for brands to enhance their global outreach.
India's trip to Ireland will kick off on Friday, August 18, which will mark the return of Jasprit Bumrah to competitive cricket following a year-long injury.
The bilateral series will be played between August 18-23, 2023 at the Malahide Cricket Club Ground.
The home team will be helmed by Paul Stirling and will look to continue its decent run after qualifying for the ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2024.
Others: The India tour of Ireland 2023 has secured three sponsorship deals with Prozeal Green Energy, Sterling Reserve, and Kore Mobile as commercial partners.
